NNAAMMEE
       pam_sge_authorize - PAM module to control access to SGE hosts

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ppaamm__ssggee__aauutthhoorriizzee [_o_p_t_i_o_n_s]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       This PAM module limits access via _s_s_h(1) etc. to Grid Engine hosts only
       to users who currently have a job running on the host.  The expectation
       is that this limits their impact on any other users of the host.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       eexxeeccdd__ssppooooll__ddiirr==_d_i_r
           Specify the spool directory in which to find the aaccttiivvee__jjoobbss direc-
           tory as _d_i_r//_h_o_s_t_n_a_m_e//aaccttiivvee__jjoobbss.  Default: //oopptt//ssggee//ddeeffaauulltt//ssppooooll.

       bbyyppaassss__uusseerrss==_u_s_e_r___l_i_s_t
           The module ignores access by users with unames in  the  comma-sepa-
           rated _u_s_e_r___l_i_s_t.  There is a limit of 30 users.

       mmaaxx__sslleeeepp==_m_a_x___s_l_e_e_p
           A  non-zero  _m_a_x___s_l_e_e_p  allows desynchronization of accesses to the
           spool directory.  The module sleeps for a random  period  _t_,  where
           0<=_t<=_m_a_x___s_l_e_e_p  microseconds before accessing the spool directory.
           This probably isn't useful.  Default: 0.

EEXXAAMMPPLLEE
       On a typical GNU/Linux system, add  something  like  the  following  to
       //eettcc//ppaamm..dd//sssshhdd, e.g. at the top.

         account required /opt/sge/lib/lx26-amd64/pam_sge_authorize.so \
           bypass_users=foo,bar,baz,qux spool_dir=/opt/sge6.2/execd_spool

       On  some  systems  it  might  be necessary to copy pam_sge_authorize.so
       into, say, //lliibb//sseeccuurriittyy, and instead use it as

         auth required pam_sge_authorize.so

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       _s_s_h(1), _p_a_m(7), _p_a_m_._c_o_n_f(4).

AAUUTTHHOORR
       TACC.  Man page by Dave Love, based on material from Bill Barth, TACC.



